Package org.knime.core.webui.data.rpc.json.impl

Class JsonRpcSingleClient<S>

java.lang.Object
org.knime.core.webui.data.rpc.AbstractRpcClient
org.knime.core.webui.data.rpc.AbstractRpcSingleClient<S>
org.knime.core.webui.data.rpc.json.impl.JsonRpcSingleClient<S>
Type Parameters:
S - the node data service interface type; defines which methods are offered by the node model to retrieve data. The parameters and return type of a method defined in the interface are subjected to serialization with an ObjectMapper. Jackson serialization works out-of-the-box on simple bean-like classes. In more advanced cases, parameter types and result types have to use Jackson annotations like JsonAutoDetect to control the serialization behavior.
All Implemented Interfaces:
RpcClient, RpcSingleClient<S>
public class JsonRpcSingleClient<S> extends AbstractRpcSingleClient<S>
A JSON-RPC based implementation of a node data service client. TODO: somehow keep backward-compatibility when a node implementer switches from a single json-rpc server to a (multi) json rpc server (the service name need to be provided in the later)
Since:
4.3
Author:
